commit.message:
CMake integration. (#62)

* Add CMake integration.

* [BUG FIX] Fix compilation:
/tmp/libQGLViewer/examples/rangeAxisConstraint/main.cpp:14:9: error: base operand of ‘->’ has non-pointer type ‘Viewer’
   14 |   viewer->setWindowTitle("rangeAxisConstraint");

* [BUG FIX] Fix compilation:
/tmp/libQGLViewer/examples/rangeAxisConstraint/viewer.cpp:26:5: error: invalid use of incomplete type ‘class qglviewer::ManipulatedFrame’
   26 |   mf->setConstraint(rac);

* OpenGL: libglu1-mesa-dev is needed.

* Kill VRender target: QGLViewer is the only target left to install.

* Install library.

>> cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/tmp/local ..
>> make all install
>> tree /tmp/local/
/tmp/local/
└── lib
    └── libQGLViewer.a

* Install headers.

>> cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/tmp/local ..
>> make all install
>>  tree /tmp/local/
/tmp/local/
├── include
│   ├── camera.h
│   ├── config.h
│   ├── constraint.h
│   ├── domUtils.h
│   ├── frame.h
│   ├── keyFrameInterpolator.h
│   ├── manipulatedCameraFrame.h
│   ├── manipulatedFrame.h
│   ├── mouseGrabber.h
│   ├── qglviewer.h
│   ├── quaternion.h
│   └── vec.h
└── lib
    ├── libQGLViewer.a

* Install pkg-config file.

>> cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/tmp/local ..
>> make all install
>>  tree /tmp/local/
/tmp/local/
├── include
│   ├── camera.h
│   ├── config.h
│   ├── constraint.h
│   ├── domUtils.h
│   ├── frame.h
│   ├── keyFrameInterpolator.h
│   ├── manipulatedCameraFrame.h
│   ├── manipulatedFrame.h
│   ├── mouseGrabber.h
│   ├── qglviewer.h
│   ├── quaternion.h
│   └── vec.h
└── lib
    ├── libQGLViewer.so
    └── pkgconfig
        └── libQGLViewer.pc
>> cat /tmp/local/lib/pkgconfig/libQGLViewer.pc
prefix=/tmp/local
exec_prefix=/tmp/local
libdir=/tmp/local/lib
includedir=/tmp/local/include/libQGLViewer

Name: libQGLViewer
Description: libQGLViewer is an open source C++ library based on Qt that eases the creation of OpenGL 3D viewers.
Version: 2.8.0
URL: https://github.com/GillesDebunne/libQGLViewer
Libs: -L${libdir} -lQGLViewer
Cflags: -I${includedir}

* Put *.h in a dedicated directory.
